      • transform

        protected void transform(int type,
             int[] dims,
             int mode,
             double[] in,
             double[] out)
        Performs a transform of the given type and dimensions on the given input/output arrays. If a cached transform doesn't exist, a new one is created and cached. Computation time initially depends on the amount of precomputation desired.
        Parameters:
        type - the kind of transform.
        dims - the dimensions of the transform.
        mode - the transform mode.
        in - the input array.
        out - the output array.
